-- Turkish Stocks: AFM Film, Akbank TAS, Akenerji Move in Istanbul
-- B y   B e n j a m i n   H a r v e y
-- 2012-02-29T16:43:25Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-29/turkish-stocks-afm-film-akenerji-turk-telekom-are-active.html
Turkeyâ€™s benchmark  ISE National 100
Index (XU100)  rose for a second day, adding 1.2 percent to 60,721.23 at
the close in Istanbul  The following stocks were active. Stock symbols are in
parentheses.  AFM Uluslararasi Film Produksiyon & Sanayi AS (AFMAS)  ,
owner of a chain of cinemas, jumped as much as 10 percent before
paring its gain to 2.1 percent at 12.45 liras. Owner Esas
Holding AS signed an agreement to sell its 89 percent stake in
the unit to Mars Sinema & Sportif Tesisler Isletmeciligi AS in
two stages. Esas will initially sell 49.4 percent of its stake
for $49 million, or $7.35 a share. It will then divest 39.6
percent at a price to be determined later, AFM said in a
statement to the  Istanbul Stock Exchange  after the market closed
yesterday.  Akbank TAS (AKBNK)  , the bank part-owned by  Citigroup
Inc. (C) , led gains among lenders and on the wider index, adding 2.9
percent to 7.02 liras. Bank stocks across Europe rose, with the
43-member Bloomberg Europe Banks and Financial Services Index up
1.3 percent, after tapping the  European Central Bank  for a
record 529.5 billion euros.  Akenerji Elektrik Uretim AS (AKENR)  , the utility owned
by  CEZ AS (CEZ)  and Akkok Group, dropped 1.4 percent to 2.19 liras,
its lowest in almost a month. Full-year loss widened to 211
million liras last year from 26.4 million liras a year earlier,
the company said in a statement to the Istanbul Stock Exchange
after the market closed yesterday. That was more than 93.5
million liras average of 17 analyst estimates compiled by
